                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     CRICKET BRIEFS
        
	Dope tests on IPL players  New Delhi: The World Anti-Doping Agency (WADA) will conduct surprise dope tests on cricketers participating in the Indian Premier League rsquo;s (IPL) from Saturday. 
  ldquo;There are surprise dope tests to begin today. The (WADA) team from Sweden has already come down. We don rsquo;t know which team will be subjected to the tests first or which player rsquo;s samples would be taken first, rdquo; said IPL commissioner Lalit Modi. ldquo;As per the ICC rules, the WADA team is here and the dope tests will start immediately, rdquo; he added.   The WADA team rsquo;s arrival comes in the close aftermath of reports in the Pakistan media that Kolkata Knight Riders rsquo; pace spearhead Shoaib Akhtar carried an unusually high number of syringes in his baggage while coming here.  
	Sourav advice for Bhajji  New Delhi: Former Team India skipper Sourav Ganguly offered off-spinner Harbhajan Singh a simple piece of advice to steer clear of controversies mdash; ldquo;control your aggression rdquo;.  ldquo;We have all (the senior players) reasoned with him and he needs to understand how vital he is to the team and so he should control himself, rdquo; Sourav said in a television interview. Harbhajan was handed a five-match ODI ban besides being barred from the remainder of the IPL for slapping India teammate Sreesanth after an IPL match last month. Sourav described Harbhajan as an aggressive but fine human being despite his on-field behaviour.  
	Tax notice to PCA  Jalandhar: Chandigarh Zone of the service tax department would issue a notice to Punjab Cricket Association (PCA) for evading service tax in the ongoing IPL at Mohali. ldquo;Some of the areas of the IPL such as event management, advertising and details of its franchise arrangements, comes under the purview of service tax. It is under consideration to issue a notice to PCA for evading the service tax, rdquo; S.D. Sra, chief commissioner of Central Excise and Customs, (Chandigarh Zone), said.   
	Nel to join Mumbai   Mumbai: South African pacer Andre Nel will join the Mumbai Indians to replace West Indies speedster Dwayne Bravo, who leaves for national duty after Sunday rsquo;s match against Deccan Chargers. Meanwhile, England batsman Kevin Pietersen has been offered a record three-year deal to play in next year rsquo;s IPL edition.  
	Sarwan to lead WI  St John's (Antigua): Middle-order batsman Ramnaresh Sarwan will lead the West Indies against Australia in the first Test at Sabina Park, Jamaica from Thursday.   
